Two persons on Friday night lost their lives after gunmen stormed the residence of the Labour Party (LP) House of Representatives candidate for Lere Federal Constituency, in Kaduna State, Suleiman Tambaya, at Gure Village in Lere Local Council of the state.  “One of the boys died on the spot, while the other died at the hospital. The case was also reported to the Divisional Police Officer and he promptly mobilise personnel to the scene of the incident.”
 
Meanwhile, there was no official confirmation from the either state police command or the state government.
 
When contacted on the telephone, the state command’s spokesman, DSP Mohammad Jalige, neither picked up his calls nor responded to the text message sent.